<dl id="un7029w"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="un7" href="#un7029">UN7: </a>  <a href="../../FF/unbs/un7all.htm#un7029w"> (V.A.2) 29(w)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> vicious circle,</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Our definition of number must not assume in advance that all numbers are finite; and we cannot in any case, without a <mark>vicious circle</mark>, use counting to define numbers, because numbers are used in counting. <small> Bertrand Russell, <a name="BRIM" href="/udra/udex.htm#BRIM"><cite title="source">Introduction to Mathematical Philosophy</cite></a> (1919), 14-15</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
